title: Police car crashes into Perth house during chase - Yahoo7
text:
Share Police car crashes into Perth house during chase - Yahoo7 An unmarked police car has crashed into a house in Perth's north, after the officer lost control during a car chase. Close Police car crashes into Perth home UP NEXT 
Officers were pursuing an allegedly stolen car on Mirrabooka Avenue in Dianella at 12.45pm on Wednesday when they lost control on Verbena Crescent and hit a gate at the front of the house, then smashed into the lounge room. 
The woman inside was treated for shock and was taken to Royal Perth Hospital for treatment. The unmarked police car crashed into a house. Source: 7 Perth 
Three officers, from the Mirrabooka Detectives office, were not hurt but the driver of the allegedly stolen car got away. 
Police are investigating the incident. Close
